The paper deals with privacy-preserving algorithms for clustering nodes in a graph, which involves techniques from data structures (cs.DS), cryptography (cs.CR), and databases (cs.DB). The paper also introduces a new algorithm for releasing an approximated minimum spanning tree topology, which falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG) and statistical learning (cs.SI).
